v2.0	2019-07-29 
  -	Added __cmapall() which calls all three funcs
  -	Checks if screen is wide enough to display cmap3h, and if it isnt, displays
  	cmap3v instead
  -	function cmap() added
  		- calls __cmapall(), piped into 'less -r -e'
  - Changed colors of text displayed to the terminals default FG color
  -	Added spacing between each color blocks by using smaller blocks to give
  	a seperation between lines (detailed below)
  - All color blocks has been changed from colored backgrounds, to colored fg
  	blocks 
  		- using the color code to color fg instead of bg and creating blocks
		  by creating strings of blank spaces.
		- blocks now consist of a string of '▆'

							      END
